  <refnamediv>
    <refname>orthfilt</refname>
    <refpurpose>orthogonal wavelet filter set</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>w:</term>
            <listitem><para> scaling filter</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>Lo_D:</term>
            <listitem><para> lowpass analysis filter</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>Hi_D:</term>
            <listitem><para> highpass analysis filter</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>Lo_R:</term>
            <listitem><para> lowpass synthesis filter</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>Hi_R:</term>
            <listitem><para> highpass synthesis filter</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
orthfilt is an utility function for obtaining analysis and synthesis filter set of given orthogonal wavelets including haar, daubechies, coiflets and symlets.
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
w=dbwavf('db2');
[lo_d,hi_d,lo_r,hi_r]=orthfilt(w);



   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

